<h1>Slack<a class="headerlink" href="#slack" title="Permalink to this headline">Â¶</a></h1>
<p>To receive updates as soon as possible, you could setup a Slack notifications.
Enable them, following these steps:</p>
<ol class="arabic">
<li><p class="first">Go to you Slack account.</p>
</li>
<li><p class="first">In channel&#8217;s dropdown menu, choose &#8220;Add a service integration...&#8221;</p>
<img alt="https://img-fotki.yandex.ru/get/6810/13558447.f/0_b36af_fdb87a97_L.png" src="https://img-fotki.yandex.ru/get/6810/13558447.f/0_b36af_fdb87a97_L.png" />
</li>
<li><p class="first">Next, filter all available integrations by &#8220;webhook&#8221; keyword.</p>
<img alt="https://img-fotki.yandex.ru/get/5500/13558447.f/0_b36ae_4eb39439_L.png" src="https://img-fotki.yandex.ru/get/5500/13558447.f/0_b36ae_4eb39439_L.png" />
</li>
<li><p class="first">And select &#8220;Incoming WebHooks&#8221;.</p>
</li>
<li><p class="first">Choose a channel to which notification should be sent by AllMyChanges.</p>
</li>
<li><p class="first">And push this huge &#8220;Add Incoming Webhook Integration&#8221; button :)</p>
</li>
<li><p class="first">Finally, copy value from &#8220;Webhook URL&#8221; field into &#8220;Slack Url field at
allmychanges&#8217;s <a class="reference external" href="https://allmychanges.com/account/settings/">account settings</a> page.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>


</div>